    <p>Pieter-Paul Verhaeghe is since October 2016 part time (50%) associated professor (docent) at the Department of Sociology of the VUB and part time (50%) post-doctoral researcher at the Department of Sociology of Ghent University. In 2012 he successfully defended his PhD about the (re)producing role of social capital for ethnic and socio-economic inequalities in health and in the labour market entrance.</p>
    <p>After obtaining his Phd, Pieter-Paul worked as a policy adviser at the Flemish Parliament on the topics of ethnic diversity, poverty and inequalities. From 2014 until 2016 he worked as a post-doctoral researcher in Sociology at Ghent University. His current research interests include the study of discrimination, migration, urban sociology, social cohesion and ethnic and socio-economic inequalities.</p>
